{
  "text": "Step 1: Encoder 1 uses the code C k to transmit each of the blocks X (1 : k, i ), i \u2208 [1, m] to the decoder. The second encoder finds the output of the code C k when Y (1 : k, i ) is fed to the code, and transmits the output vector on X 22 (1 : n, i ) . The encoder uses an interleaving method similar to the one in [CITATION_1] to transmit Z . For the sequence Z (1 : k, 1 : m) , it finds the output of C km for this input and transmits it on X 21 (1 : n, 1 : m) .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "17569856"
